# Kubernetes Hands-on with KIND

## Official Documentation

https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/docs/user/quick-start

---

# What is KIND?

**KIND = Kubernetes IN Docker**

Instead of creating real VMs or cloud instances, KIND creates Kubernetes nodes as Docker containers.


Laptop
 └── Docker
      └── Kind Cluster
            ├── Control Plane
            ├── Worker Node 1
            └── Worker Node 2


## Benefits

- Free
- Lightweight
- Fast Setup
- Perfect for Learning Kubernetes
- Runs Completely on Local Machine

